Rewrite these files to the new contract, keeping what is still true and deleting what is dead (kinds routing tables, lanes, digest suppression, priority mappings as policy):

1. `skills/messaging/SKILL.md` — the fleet-facing skill. Producers: `joelclaw notify send "<text>"` unchanged, everything (kind, priority, `--data`) is evidence, never instruction; no deprecation nagging; the agent decides delivery, timing, formatting, platform; every decision has a stream receipt (`joelclaw messages trace <flowId>` still works); the dead-simple fallback marks `⚠️ fallback:` messages; single-poller doctrine survives (one transport, one gateway session — never spawn a listener or a second gateway).
2. `docs/gateway.md` — operations: transport daemon (slim), the gateway session + driver panes in workspace `[jc] gateway agent`, heartbeat key `gateway:agent:heartbeat`, kill drill, rollback script `scripts/gateway-cutover-rollback.sh`.
3. `docs/cli.md` — the notify section only.

Do not touch `.brain/projects/**` step files or the plugin prompts. Work autonomously, do not commit, print a DONE summary.
